#: ../../tv-typewriters.rst:5
msgid "TV Typewriters: A Tale of Hackish Ingenuity"
msgstr "TVタイプライター:ハッカー的創意の物語"

#: ../../tv-typewriters.rst:7
msgid ""
"Here is a true story about a glass tty: One day an MIT hacker was in a "
"motorcycle accident and broke his leg. He had to stay in the hospital quite "
"a while, and got restless because he couldn't :ref:`hack`\\. Two of his "
"friends therefore took a terminal and a modem for it to the hospital, so "
"that he could use the computer by telephone from his hospital bed."
msgstr ""
"ここにグラスtty(ガラス製のtty)にまつわる実話がある。ある日、MITのハッカーがバイク事故にあって脚を折った。彼はかなり長く入院しなければならず、\\"
" :ref:`hack`\\ "
"できないので落ち着かなくなった。そこで二人の友人が端末とそのためのモデムを病院に持ち込み、彼が病室のベッドから電話でコンピュータを使えるようにした。"

#: ../../tv-typewriters.rst:11
msgid ""
"Now this happened some years before the spread of home computers, and "
"computer terminals were not a familiar sight to the average person. When the"
" two friends got to the hospital, a guard stopped them and asked what they "
"were carrying. They explained that they wanted to take a computer terminal "
"to their friend who was a patient."
msgstr ""
"さて、これは家庭用コンピュータが普及するより数年前のことで、コンピュータ端末は一般の人にはなじみのない代物だった。二人の友人が病院に着くと、警備員が彼らを止めて何を運んでいるのか尋ねた。彼らは、患者である友人のところにコンピュータ端末を持っていきたいのだと説明した。"

#: ../../tv-typewriters.rst:15
msgid ""
"The guard got out his list of things that patients were permitted to have in"
" their rooms: TV, radio, electric razor, typewriter, tape player, ... no "
"computer terminals. Computer terminals weren't on the list, so the guard "
"wouldn't let it in. Rules are rules, you know. (This guard was clearly a "
":ref:`droid`\\.)"
msgstr ""
"警備員は、患者が病室に持ち込んでよいものの一覧を取り出した。TV、ラジオ、電気カミソリ、タイプライター、テーププレーヤー……コンピュータ端末はない。コンピュータ端末は一覧になかったので、警備員は中に入れさせなかった。規則は規則だからね。(この警備員は明らかに\\"
" :ref:`droid`\\ だった。)"

#: ../../tv-typewriters.rst:20
msgid ""
"Fair enough, said the two friends, and they left again. They were "
"frustrated, of course, because they knew that the terminal was as harmless "
"as a TV or anything else on the list... which gave them an idea."
msgstr ""
"もっともだ、と二人の友人は言って、また帰っていった。もちろん彼らは苛立った。端末がTVや一覧の他のどれとも同じくらい無害だと知っていたからである……そしてそれが彼らにある考えを与えた。"

#: ../../tv-typewriters.rst:23
msgid ""
"The next day they returned, and the same thing happened: a guard stopped "
"them and asked what they were carrying. They said: \"This is a TV "
"typewriter!\" The guard was skeptical, so they plugged it in and "
"demonstrated it. \"See? You just type on the keyboard and what you type "
"shows up on the TV screen.\" Now the guard didn't stop to think about how "
"utterly useless a typewriter would be that didn't produce any paper copies "
"of what you typed; but this was clearly a TV typewriter, no doubt about it. "
"So he checked his list: “A TV is all right, a typewriter is all right ... "
"okay, take it on in!”"
msgstr ""
"翌日、彼らは戻ってきて、同じことが起きた。警備員が彼らを止めて何を運んでいるのか尋ねた。彼らは言った。「これはTVタイプライターです!」警備員は半信半疑だったので、彼らはそれをつないで実演した。「ほら、キーボードで打つと、打ったものがTVの画面に表示されるんです」。さて警備員は、打ったものの紙のコピーをまったく出さないタイプライターがいかに無用の長物かを立ち止まって考えはしなかった。だがこれは明らかにTVタイプライターであり、それは間違いない。そこで彼は一覧を確認した。「TVはよし、タイプライターもよし……よし、持っていきな!」"

#: ../../tv-typewriters.rst:31
msgid ""
"[Historical note: Many years ago, *PopularElectronics* published solder-it-"
"yourself plans for a TV typewriter. Despite the essential uselessness of the"
" device, it was an enormously popular project. Steve Ciarcia, the man behind"
" *Byte* magazine's \"Circuit Cellar\" feature, resurrected this ghost in one"
" of his books of the early 1980s. He ascribed its popularity (no doubt "
"correctly) to the feeling of power the builder could achieve by being able "
"to decide himself what would be shown on the TV. And, in fact, the device "
"was not entirely useless; when combined with a modem board, it became a "
"crude but serviceable terminal. —ESR]"
msgstr ""
"[歴史的注記:何年も前、\\ *PopularElectronics*\\ "
"がTVタイプライターのはんだ付け自作プランを掲載した。装置の本質的な無用さにもかかわらず、それは途方もなく人気のあるプロジェクトだった。\\ "
"*Byte*\\ 誌の「Circuit Cellar」連載を手がけた人物、Steve "
"Ciarciaは、1980年代初頭の自著の一冊でこの亡霊を蘇らせた。彼はその人気を(疑いなく正しく)、TVに何を表示するかを自分で決められることで作り手が得られる力の感覚に帰した。そして実際、その装置はまったく無用というわけではなかった。モデムボードと組み合わせると、粗削りだが使える端末になったのである。――ESR]"

#: ../../tv-typewriters.rst:38
msgid ""
"[Antihistorical note: On September 23rd, 1992, the L.A. Times ran the "
"following bit in Steve Harvey's ‘Only in L.A.' column:"
msgstr ""
"[反歴史的注記:1992年9月23日、L.A. TimesはSteve Harveyの‘Only in L.A.'コラムに次の一節を載せた。"

#: ../../tv-typewriters.rst:53
msgid ""
"I have since investigated this matter and determined that many of today's "
"teenagers have never seen a slide rule, either.... --ESR]"
msgstr "私はその後この件を調査し、今日のティーンエイジャーの多くが計算尺さえ見たことがないことを突き止めた……。――ESR]"
